%N A394999 Decimal expansion of gamma*phi, where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant and phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 is the golden ratio.
%C A394999 It is not known whether this constant is irrational or transcendental.
%F A394999 Equals A001620 * A001622.
%e A394999 0.93395456464954989517284750098623200465426838097822813...
%t A394999 RealDigits[EulerGamma*GoldenRatio, 10, 105][[1]]
%o A394999 (PARI) default(realprecision, 50); Euler*(1+sqrt(5))/2
%o A394999 (Python) from mpmath import mp, euler, phi; mp.dps=50; print(euler*phi)
%Y A394999 Cf. A001620 (Euler-Mascheroni constant gamma), A001622 (golden ratio phi).
%K A394999 nonn,cons
%O A394999 0,1
